root.pub-comments: The languages under the Dravidian and Uralic subgroups are not intended to represent a formal subgrouping by the author, but are rather the languages that the author used to build evidence for the relationship of the Dravidian and Uralic language families based on a sound correspondence analysis of the two language families.
root.publications: Burrow, Thomas. 1968. Collected papers on Dravidian linguistics. India: Annamalai University.
